  "description": "In the fantasy world of Teraum, there is a character named Barnabus Trent, who for a while ran a shop in the town of Bellybrush. That town sold items gathered from all over Teraum… but most were from such distant lands that any context or meaning they had beyond “pretty trinket,” was lost.\nA drawing (by Stirling Little) of the alligator that hung from the ceiling of Barnabus’ shop. Rumor had it he let it loose at night to stop burglars but wrestled it back up to the ceiling each morning. More than one farmboy signed up to sail to Gnalens after seeing the alligator.\n",
  "name": "Barnabus hawking trinkets to the",
